---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Insurance for International Restaurant Managers | Compare Expat Plans";
const description = "Health insurance guide for Restaurant Managers working internationally, covering food service management positions abroad, hospitality careers, and global restaurant management opportunities.";
const headline = "Insurance for International Restaurant Managers";
const subheadline = "Coverage solutions for Restaurant Managers working abroad, leading food service operations internationally, and pursuing careers across restaurants and hospitality venues worldwide.";
const canonicalPath = "/guides/restaurant-manager-insurance";
const heroBackgroundImage = "/images/guides/restaurant-manager-insurance-hero.png";

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', label: 'Overview' },
  { id: 'coverage-needs', label: 'Coverage Needs' },
  { id: 'work-settings', label: 'Work Settings' },
  { id: 'credentials', label: 'Credentials' },
  { id: 'occupational-health', label: 'Occupational Health' },
  { id: 'work-demands', label: 'Work Demands' },
  { id: 'career-considerations', label: 'Career Considerations' },
  { id: 'faqs', label: 'FAQs' },
  { id: 'next-steps', label: 'Next Steps' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title={title}
  description={description}
  headline={headline}
  subheadline={subheadline}
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  heroBackgroundImage={heroBackgroundImage}
  tocItems={tocItems}
>
  <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

    <section id="overview">
      <h2>International Restaurant Manager Careers</h2>
      <p>
        Restaurant Managers oversee daily operations, staff, guest experience, and financial performance of dining establishments. International restaurant management offers opportunities to lead venues in diverse culinary markets, work with global restaurant groups, and develop expertise across different dining cultures.
      </p>
      <p>
        International restaurant management opportunities exist through international restaurant chains, hotel F&B operations, cruise lines, and restaurant groups expanding into global markets.
      </p>
      <p>
        This guide addresses insurance considerations for Restaurant Managers working abroad across restaurants and hospitality venues worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="coverage-needs">
      <h2>Coverage Needs for Restaurant Managers</h2>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={[
          { key: 'need', header: 'Coverage Need' },
          { key: 'why', header: 'Why It Matters' },
          { key: 'typical', header: 'Coverage Situation?' },
        ]}
        rows={[
          { need: 'General health coverage', why: 'Professional health maintenance', typical: 'Usually employer-provided' },
          { need: 'Injury coverage', why: 'Kitchen and floor hazards', typical: 'Essential for role' },
          { need: 'Ergonomic coverage', why: 'Extended standing and movement', typical: 'Important for role' },
          { need: 'Mental health support', why: 'High-pressure service environment', typical: 'Consider including' },
          { need: 'Wellness support', why: 'Long hours and shift work', typical: 'Often included' },
          { need: 'Emergency coverage', why: 'Incident response responsibilities', typical: 'Essential for role' },
        ]}
      />

      <h3>Physical Work Environment</h3>
      <p>
        Restaurant managers spend long hours on their feet, moving between front-of-house and kitchen areas. The environment includes heat exposure from kitchens, slip hazards, and physical demands of service. Injury coverage and ergonomic support address these occupational realities.
      </p>
      <p>
        Burns, cuts, and slip injuries occur even for managers who occasionally assist during busy periods.
      </p>

      <h3>High-Pressure Service</h3>
      <p>
        Restaurant service involves intense pressure during peak hours—coordinating staff, ensuring quality, managing timing, and handling guest expectations simultaneously. The pace and intensity create significant stress. Mental health support helps sustain long-term restaurant careers.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-settings">
      <h2>Coverage by Work Setting</h2>

      <h3>Fine Dining</h3>
      <p>
        Upscale restaurant or Michelin venue. Premium benefits often. High standards and pressure. Fine dining offers prestige.
      </p>

      <h3>Hotel F&B</h3>
      <p>
        Hotel restaurant or F&B operation. Hotel chain benefits. Multiple outlets possible. Hotels offer stability.
      </p>

      <h3>Restaurant Group</h3>
      <p>
        Multi-location restaurant company. Group benefits. Career mobility. Groups offer growth.
      </p>

      <h3>Cruise Line</h3>
      <p>
        Cruise ship dining operations. Maritime benefits package. Unique environment. Cruises offer adventure.
      </p>

      <h3>Independent</h3>
      <p>
        Independent restaurant venue. Benefits vary significantly. Owner relationship. Independents offer flexibility.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Coverage for Restaurant Managers"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Restaurant Managers working abroad across restaurants and hospitality venues worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Restaurant Manager Plans"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

    <section id="credentials">
      <h2>Credentials and Professional Recognition</h2>

      <h3>Hospitality Degree</h3>
      <p>
        Hospitality or culinary management degree. Professional training. Academic foundation. Degrees demonstrate commitment.
      </p>

      <h3>Service Experience</h3>
      <p>
        Progressive restaurant experience. Front-of-house expertise. Service excellence. Experience builds capability.
      </p>

      <h3>Food Safety</h3>
      <p>
        Food safety certifications. HACCP knowledge. Compliance understanding. Certifications often required.
      </p>

      <h3>Beverage Knowledge</h3>
      <p>
        Wine and beverage expertise. Sommelier training. Bar management. Beverage knowledge adds value.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="occupational-health">
      <h2>Occupational Health Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Physical Demands</h3>
      <p>
        Standing for shifts. Floor movement. Physical assistance. Ergonomic coverage important.
      </p>

      <h3>Service Pressure</h3>
      <p>
        Peak hour intensity. Guest expectations. Quality standards. Mental health support valuable.
      </p>

      <h3>Hazard Exposure</h3>
      <p>
        Kitchen environment. Slip risks. Heat exposure. Injury coverage essential.
      </p>

      <h3>Schedule Demands</h3>
      <p>
        Evening and weekend work. Split shifts. Holiday coverage. Wellness support helpful.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-demands">
      <h2>Managing Work Demands</h2>

      <h3>Service</h3>
      <p>
        Guest experience management. Service flow. Quality assurance. Service creates reputation.
      </p>

      <h3>Staff</h3>
      <p>
        Team scheduling. Training programs. Performance management. Staff enables service.
      </p>

      <h3>Operations</h3>
      <p>
        Inventory management. Vendor relationships. Compliance oversight. Operations support quality.
      </p>

      <h3>Financial</h3>
      <p>
        Cost management. Revenue optimization. P&L responsibility. Financial health drives success.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="career-considerations">
      <h2>Career Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Steady Demand</h3>
      <p>
        Dining culture global. Restaurant growth continuing. Management talent needed. Demand steady.
      </p>

      <h3>Career Paths</h3>
      <p>
        General Manager. Operations Director. F&B Director. Restaurant owner. Multiple paths available.
      </p>

      <h3>Credential Portability</h3>
      <p>
        Service skills universal. Hospitality training transfers. Management ability portable. Credentials transferable.
      </p>

      <h3>Field Evolution</h3>
      <p>
        Technology integration. Sustainability focus. Delivery platforms. Field evolving rapidly.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="faqs">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">I'm a restaurant manager considering international work. What should I know?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Restaurant groups and hotels provide benefits. International experience valued. Service skills transfer. Culinary markets differ.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do employers provide international coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Hotel and chain restaurants often yes. Independent restaurants vary. Verify coverage carefully. Cruise lines typically comprehensive.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Are physical demands a significant concern?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Yes in restaurant work. Long hours standing. Physical environment. Ergonomic and injury coverage important.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do restaurant skills transfer internationally?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Service excellence universal. Management skills transfer. Culinary styles vary. Adaptability important.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is work-life balance achievable?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Challenging in restaurants. Evening and weekend work standard. Lifestyle consideration. Balance requires boundaries.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What's the career outlook?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Dining culture expanding globally. Quality management valued. Career paths available. Outlook positive.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="next-steps">
      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <p>
        Start by evaluating employer benefits packages. Ensure injury coverage for physical work environment. Prioritize ergonomic support for demanding schedules. Verify international coverage scope for your venue location.
      </p>
      <p>
        Restaurant Managers create dining experiences worldwide. Your coverage should support restaurant management careers—addressing physical and service demands, covering health maintenance, and protecting you across hospitality work worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Protect Your Restaurant Management Career"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Restaurant Managers working abroad across restaurants and hospitality venues worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

  </article>
</PageShell>
